HEADWORD: Disintegrable
<hw>Dis*in"te*gra*ble</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Capable of
being disintegrated, or reduced to fragments or powder.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Argillo-calcite is readily <qex>disintegrable</qex> by
exposure.</q> <rj><qau>Kirwan.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Disintegrate</ent>⟦br⟧
